nists. The COVID-19 pandemic has exacerbated misogyny and related systemic inequalities. Yet it has also revived feminist mobilization and animated calls for a new and comprehensive equality agenda for Canada. Feminism’s Fight tells the crucial story of a transformation in how feminism has been treated by governments and asks how new ways of organizing and new alliances can advance a feminist agenda of social and economic equality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh1 aBernhardt, Nicole S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriskin, Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Barbara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCattapan, Alana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDay, Shelagh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobrowolsky, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFindlay, Tammy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFletcher, Amber J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGabriel, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGotell, Lise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuxton, Meg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuxton, Meg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPalmater, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPorter, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eB